{[showcards W:DK N:D2]

The bidding has been as shown. Partner led the \DK, dummy played low 

Play the \DJ.

Put yourself in partner's shoes. He almost surely has \D K Q 10 x (x). When South holds up on his \DA, which he almost surely will, West may think he is holding up with \D A J x, and be afraid to continue the suit.

You can help your partner figure out the true situation by merely playing your \DJ so he can see that South doesn't have it.

With this good play West will be able to continue \Ds and defeat the contract.}
[Play "W"]DK

